						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Viḷambi (1539)</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is in Telugu and seems to be connected with No. 437. Mentions <hi rend="bold">Veṅgaḷayya</hi> as the son of <hi rend="bold">Pōchirāja-Timmaya</hi> of the Kauṇḍinyagōtra. The details of the date viz. <hi rend="bold">Viḷambi, Māgha, śu. 11 may be equated to 1539 A.D., January 30, but cannot be verified.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
